  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Mrs. Lucy A. Browne is sending a small bundle of items prepared by herself and her daughters for the anti-slavery fair. She hopes to see Maria Weston Chapman in Sudbury and believes that if she pleaded there for the slave, she might possibly rouse the people from their lethargy. Lucy A. Browne believes that &quot;C. C. Burleigh had not the power, &amp; I fear no human being has.&quot;</subfield>
